    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES62-5A, ES62-5D, ES67-5A AND
        ES67-5D - REASSEMBLY - SHIFT TOWER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHIFT TOWER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Standard Shift Tower</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301070">Figure 70</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301070" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301070" filename="../figg13/g1301070.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 70. Standard Shift Tower</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HANDLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SHIFT LEVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RETAINER LOCK PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. ROCK SHAFT PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. GASKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. LEVER HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. SNAP RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. LEVER COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. SPRING RETAINER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the lever housing on edge in a vise.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold the shift lever so that the lever cross hole aligns with the rock shaft cross hole
                    in the lever housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the rock shaft pin through the holes in the lever housing and shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the rock shaft snap ring to the groove of the lever housing, locking the rock
                    shaft in place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Next, place a new, lightly greased seal on the lever housing. Grease the inner wall of
                    the cup, and slide it over the lever into position on the dome.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the spring, spring retainer, and lever cover over the shift lever. Depress the
                    spring retainer and insert the spring retainer lock pin through the hole in the lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the shift lever handle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the shift lever and lever housing assembly on the shifter housing with a gasket,
                    noting that the finger enters the neutral position notches.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the assembly with the bolts and lockwashers. Tighten to 25 to 41 ft-lbs. (34-56 N&#8226;
                    m).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Gimbal Shift Tower</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301071">Figure 71</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301071" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301071" filename="../figg13/g1301071.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 71. Gimbal Shift Tower</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CABLE STRAP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. YOKE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TRUNNION SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SHIFT TOWER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. PIVOT PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. SHIFT LEVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. BOOT</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. SHIFT KNOB</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the yoke onto the shift lever. Secure the yoke by pressing the pivot pin into
                    position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the lever assembly into the tower housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>The raised boss on the yoke must be placed next to the side of the tower that contains the
                        casting number stamp.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the two trunnion screws and tighten to 100 to 125 ft-lbs. (136 to 170 N&#8226;
                    m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the boot into place. Secure it with two tie cables, being careful not to cut into
                    the boot.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
